prompts.readme_coverage_check:
Check if this GitHub Issue is already covered in the README or pinned issues:

README: {readme_content}

Pinned Issues: {pinned_issues_content}

Title: {issue_title}
Body: {issue_body}

Is the EXACT same question/issue clearly and completely addressed in the README or pinned issues?

IMPORTANT: Only mark as COVERED if you are 100% certain the exact issue is clearly explained with sufficient detail in the existing documentation.

Respond ONLY with:
- `COVERED` - ONLY if 100% certain the exact issue is clearly covered
- `NOT_COVERED` - if not covered or if uncertain

prompts.content_quality_check:
Analyze the quality and clarity of this GitHub Issue:

Title: {issue_title}
Body: {issue_body}
Template: {template_analysis}

Evaluate the issue quality:

Respond ONLY with:
- `UNCLEAR` - if too vague, lacks details, or needs more information
- `BASIC` - if about basic usage, installation, or elementary concepts that can be easily found through documentation or search engines
- `VALID` - if clear, detailed, and appropriate for the project level

prompts.pr_spam_detection:
Analyze this GitHub PR for spam content:

Title: {pr_title}
Body: {pr_body}
Changes: {file_changes}

Is this spam or meaningless content?
Spam indicators: random characters, advertisements, malicious content, completely unrelated content, obvious test submissions, meaningless file changes.

Respond ONLY with:
- `SPAM` - if spam or meaningless content
- `NOT_SPAM` - if legitimate content (even if low quality)

prompts.pr_quality_check:
Analyze the quality of this GitHub PR:

Title: {pr_title}
Body: {pr_body}
Changes: {file_changes}

Evaluate the PR quality and purpose:

Respond ONLY with:
- `UNCLEAR` - if purpose is unclear or lacks proper description
- `MALICIOUS` - if changes appear malicious or harmful
- `TRIVIAL` - if changes are meaningless or just testing
- `VALID` - if clear, purposeful, and legitimate

prompts.readme_relevance:
Analyze if this GitHub Issue is related to content in the README:

README Content: {readme_content}

Issue Title: {issue_title}
Issue Body: {issue_body}

Is this issue asking about something that is already explained or covered in the README?

Respond ONLY with:
- `RELATED` - if the issue is asking about content covered in README
- `NOT_RELATED` - if the issue is not about README content

prompts.readme_answer:
Based on the README content, provide a brief and direct answer to this GitHub Issue:

README Content: {readme_content}

Issue Title: {issue_title}
Issue Body: {issue_body}

Provide a concise answer in Chinese. Focus on the key information and avoid lengthy explanations. If applicable, mention the relevant section in README.
